<HEADLINE> Albright Plans Stop in Papua New Guinea to Show Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 20 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will visit Papua New Guinea next week to offer
U.S. support to the South pacific nation for its effort to recover
from a devastating tidal wave, the State Department said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman James Rubin said Albright is to fly to Port Moresby
on July 29 on her way to Australia from the annual conference of
the South East Asian countries in Manila, the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The United States has provided assistance to Papua New Guinea
by offering 25,000 U.S. dollars through its embassy, Rubin said.
"And we are also looking for other ways to help."
</P>
<P>
"Our embassy is in the process of assessing needs in
consultation with the government, and we will be in a position
to determine how the U.S. can be helpful following that
assessment," Rubin said.  
</P>
